Current failing errors (from the final build log)
- 2 compilation errors in CoverPhotoController:
  - incompatible types: String cannot be converted to Instant
    - cp.setFetchedAt(request.fetchedAt);
    - cp.setLastProcessedAt(request.lastProcessedAt);

Cause
- I updated CoverPhoto.fetchedAt and CoverPhoto.lastProcessedAt to type Instant, but the CoverPhotoController (request DTO) still provides those values as String. The controller code attempts to assign String to Instant fields, causing the compiler errors.

Recommended fix (exact change to apply)
- Convert the incoming String fields to Instant when setting the entity fields (defensive parsing). Example replacement code (update CoverPhotoController imports and these two assignments):

Add import:
import java.time.Instant;

Replace:
cp.setFetchedAt(request.fetchedAt);
cp.setLastProcessedAt(request.lastProcessedAt);

With:
if (request.fetchedAt != null && !request.fetchedAt.isBlank()) {
    try {
        cp.setFetchedAt(Instant.parse(request.fetchedAt));
    } catch (Exception e) {
        // fallback: leave null or set to Instant.now() depending on business rule
        cp.setFetchedAt(null);
    }
} else {
    cp.setFetchedAt(null);
}

if (request.lastProcessedAt != null && !request.lastProcessedAt.isBlank()) {
    try {
        cp.setLastProcessedAt(Instant.parse(request.lastProcessedAt));
    } catch (Exception e) {
        cp.setLastProcessedAt(null);
    }
} else {
    cp.setLastProcessedAt(null);
}

Alternative (option B)
- Change the request DTO in CoverPhotoController to declare fetchedAt and lastProcessedAt as Instant instead of String and accept Instant directly (requires request JSON to be ISO-8601 and Jackson can map to Instant). This is more type-safe but may require API contract change.

